			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I play mage and cleric as my two main characters, and I have for almost five years now.
<br />

<br />
Clerics do NOT have invis. Please do not spread mis-information. They have ITU (Invis to Undead), and only ITU, and always have had ITU.
<br />

<br />
Clerics do not NEED invis. Sure, I can use it, it would make life easier, but why the hell make the game EASIER? Isn't it too easy already?
<br />

<br />
Mages do not NEED root. Sure, I can use this too, it would make life even easier, but why the hell make the game EVEN EASIER?
<br />

<br />
Fanaskin, if you keep dieing, you are doing something wrong. Perhaps post the details of what you are doing when you keep dieing, and you will perhaps get some advice? But if you love necros so much, why not play one instead?
<br />

<br />
There are some arguments that our pets are still too weak to justify our lack of defensive spells, but the fix for this if it remains an issue is to boost those pets, NOT give us the spells of other classes, further blurring class boundaries. 
<br />

<br />
EverQuest is a class based game, every class is not meant to get the abilities of every other class. EverQuest does not need watering down to remove every last remnant of skill it requires.
<br />

<br />
Suzanna.<br />_________________<br />Arch Convoker Suzanna Dreamingheart
<br />
Mighty Mage!
<br />
<a href=http://p208.ezboard.com/bheroes795> Heroes of the Old Lands </a>
<br />
Lanys T'Vyl.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
