There are other pet classes? <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" />
<br />
Seriously, if we worry about stepping on toes that shouldn't be by our foot anyway we will never get anywhere. Just like a Beatlord shouldn't get upset when Shaman get boosts in slow/buffs and such, or a Druid get upset if a Cleric recieves better buffs. It's not an end (as healing or tanking) but an upgrade to our means- one that should always be ours.
<br />

<br />
(INC angry Churizo in 10, 9....)
<br />

<br />
Honestly what I want is the pet that should be able to defend us as well as the pet that can shred all opposition. However, the devs seem content to give us weak, flimsy pets- 
<br />

<br />
Honestly have you Mages who are "in the know" spoken to the Devs about this? I would honestly love an open response from them about our pet power and if they really think that this is where we should stand. Because if they really have no intention of fixing us, I want to know so I can preorder WoW. I am tired of the expansion run around (we'll look at it after X launch, then after we fix the bugs, then you know Y launch is right around the corner...), I am tired of the dev public silence and apathy towards Mages (we hear about invis on the BL boards, the "I'm looking into it" lie, we rarely get Dev posts here and when we do it's to tell us of a nerf or to say "Yep, it's a bug" and never anything concrete to calm the tempest...) and I am tired of marginal upgrades to weak spells being considered usefull. 
<br />

<br />
